[
    {
        "text": "Science: perhaps man's greatest tool in understanding how the world works.",
        "startTime": 202,
        "endTime": 6406,
        "slowStartTime": 453,
        "slowEndTime": 9834
    },
    {
        "text": "But does it lead us to truth?",
        "startTime": 7333,
        "endTime": 9830,
        "slowStartTime": 11149,
        "slowEndTime": 14970
    },
    {
        "text": "German philosopher, Friedrich Nietzsche, was an avid science enthusiast.",
        "startTime": 11067,
        "endTime": 15475,
        "slowStartTime": 16751,
        "slowEndTime": 23438
    },
    {
        "text": "But, he also recognized that even science has its limitations.",
        "startTime": 15923,
        "endTime": 20455,
        "slowStartTime": 24034,
        "slowEndTime": 30907
    },
    {
        "text": "See, science touts the ability to explain the world,...",
        "startTime": 20946,
        "endTime": 24711,
        "slowStartTime": 31569,
        "slowEndTime": 37291
    },
    {
        "text": "...when, according to Nietzsche, it can only describe it.",
        "startTime": 24919,
        "endTime": 28243,
        "slowStartTime": 37528,
        "slowEndTime": 42590
    },
    {
        "text": "For example, science might attempt to explain why fire burns...",
        "startTime": 30294,
        "endTime": 34505,
        "slowStartTime": 45591,
        "slowEndTime": 51982
    },
    {
        "text": "...by saying it's an exothermic combination of a combustible material with oxygen.",
        "startTime": 34587,
        "endTime": 38249,
        "slowStartTime": 52031,
        "slowEndTime": 57599
    },
    {
        "text": "That certainly describes how fire burns, but it doesn't quite address why.",
        "startTime": 39539,
        "endTime": 43971,
        "slowStartTime": 59458,
        "slowEndTime": 66181
    },
    {
        "text": "As in, \"Why does fire exist the way that it does?\"",
        "startTime": 45147,
        "endTime": 48833,
        "slowStartTime": 67870,
        "slowEndTime": 73475
    },
    {
        "text": "Although science has allowed us to describe the world in greater detail,...",
        "startTime": 50613,
        "endTime": 54093,
        "slowStartTime": 76070,
        "slowEndTime": 81364
    },
    {
        "text": "...we're still completely clueless as to the meaning behind it all.",
        "startTime": 54423,
        "endTime": 57767,
        "slowStartTime": 81785,
        "slowEndTime": 86876
    },
    {
        "text": "As the philosopher who famously said, \"God is dead,\"...",
        "startTime": 60051,
        "endTime": 63313,
        "slowStartTime": 90226,
        "slowEndTime": 95195
    },
    {
        "text": "...it's obvious that he isn't criticizing science in favor of religion.",
        "startTime": 63525,
        "endTime": 67252,
        "slowStartTime": 95437,
        "slowEndTime": 101103
    },
    {
        "text": "But, he recognizes this dilemma.",
        "startTime": 68043,
        "endTime": 70212,
        "slowStartTime": 102214,
        "slowEndTime": 105543
    },
    {
        "text": "Religion attempts to answer the question of meaning,...",
        "startTime": 71201,
        "endTime": 73688,
        "slowStartTime": 106952,
        "slowEndTime": 110757
    },
    {
        "text": "...but the achievements of science have cast doubt on such beliefs.",
        "startTime": 73783,
        "endTime": 78187,
        "slowStartTime": 110824,
        "slowEndTime": 117505
    },
    {
        "text": "Science may try to fill this void of meaning,...",
        "startTime": 78479,
        "endTime": 81309,
        "slowStartTime": 117869,
        "slowEndTime": 122188
    },
    {
        "text": "...but it can't, because, as Nietzsche said,...",
        "startTime": 82159,
        "endTime": 85081,
        "slowStartTime": 123388,
        "slowEndTime": 127846
    },
    {
        "text": "...\"Science has no consideration for ultimate purposes.\"",
        "startTime": 85365,
        "endTime": 88969,
        "slowStartTime": 128198,
        "slowEndTime": 133678
    },
    {
        "text": "Problem for Nietzsche is most people don't recognize this limitation,...",
        "startTime": 89476,
        "endTime": 93543,
        "slowStartTime": 134364,
        "slowEndTime": 140540
    },
    {
        "text": "...and instead, worship science as a kind of new religion,...",
        "startTime": 93671,
        "endTime": 97924,
        "slowStartTime": 140656,
        "slowEndTime": 147111
    },
    {
        "text": "...an objective value for a godless age.",
        "startTime": 98744,
        "endTime": 101511,
        "slowStartTime": 148266,
        "slowEndTime": 152492
    },
    {
        "text": "Just turn on the telly and you'll see how even science can become evangelized.",
        "startTime": 102299,
        "endTime": 107698,
        "slowStartTime": 153599,
        "slowEndTime": 161772
    },
    {
        "text": "\"And that is a scientific fact.\"",
        "startTime": 108189,
        "endTime": 110306,
        "slowStartTime": 162433,
        "slowEndTime": 165684
    },
    {
        "text": "\"Because the Bible says so.\"",
        "startTime": 110523,
        "endTime": 112213,
        "slowStartTime": 165934,
        "slowEndTime": 168544
    },
    {
        "text": "\"Proven by real science.\"",
        "startTime": 112355,
        "endTime": 114455,
        "slowStartTime": 168682,
        "slowEndTime": 171908
    },
    {
        "text": "\"It is God's will.\"",
        "startTime": 114543,
        "endTime": 116964,
        "slowStartTime": 171964,
        "slowEndTime": 175671
    },
    {
        "text": "Nietzsche dares us to take a step further,...",
        "startTime": 118200,
        "endTime": 120565,
        "slowStartTime": 177450,
        "slowEndTime": 181072
    },
    {
        "text": "...to not only think critically of religion,...",
        "startTime": 121001,
        "endTime": 123250,
        "slowStartTime": 181652,
        "slowEndTime": 185100
    },
    {
        "text": "...but to think critically of knowledge itself.",
        "startTime": 123537,
        "endTime": 126027,
        "slowStartTime": 185456,
        "slowEndTime": 189265
    },
    {
        "text": "For, worshipping knowledge for knowledge's sake can lead to dire consequences.",
        "startTime": 126643,
        "endTime": 131856,
        "slowStartTime": 190114,
        "slowEndTime": 198009
    },
    {
        "text": "As he said, \"Man shouldn't be the servant of knowledge...\"",
        "startTime": 138572,
        "endTime": 142237,
        "slowStartTime": 208008,
        "slowEndTime": 213581
    },
    {
        "text": "...\"knowledge should be the servant of man.\"",
        "startTime": 142799,
        "endTime": 145411,
        "slowStartTime": 214348,
        "slowEndTime": 218341
    }
]